The paper proposes an approach for automatic repair of bugs in Java programs, specifically focusing on conditional statements. This falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The approach involves runtime trace collection and Satisfiability Modulo Theory (SMT), which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates the approach on real-world bugs, which involves empirical analysis (cs.CR). Finally, the approach can be applied to a variety of Java programs, which falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) category.
